{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1e2a323f-4ac2-440b-b79b-844cb94f0306","content":"No workflow files found in the current directory, so here's a general guide for the switch:\n\n### Changes needed for NuGet Trusted Publishing (OIDC)\n\n**1. Add `permissions` to your workflow job:**\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token request\n      contents: read\n```\n\n**2. Replace the `dotnet nuget push` step:**\n\nBefore:\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n    --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n    --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}\n```\n\nAfter:\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n    --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n    --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}\n```\n↓ becomes ↓\n```yaml\n- uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4  # if not already present\n\n- run: |\n    dotnet nuget add source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json \\\n      --name nuget.org \\\n      --trusted-publisher github \\\n      --owner <YOUR_GITHUB_ORG_OR_USER> \\\n      --configfile nuget.config\n    dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source nuget.org\n```\n\n**3. Configure NuGet.org side:**\n- Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → (your package) → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add a new GitHub Actions publisher with:\n  - **Repository owner**: your GitHub org/user\n  - **Repository name**: your repo\n  - **Workflow filename**: e.g. `publish.yml`\n  - Optionally restrict to a specific **environment** or **ref**\n\n**4. Remove the secret:**\nOnce verified, delete `NUGET_API_KEY` from your repo/org secrets.\n\n### Summary of key differences\n\n| | API Key | Trusted Publishing |\n|---|---|---|\n| Secret management | Manual rotation | None (OIDC) |\n| Permission scope | `id-token: write` not needed | `id-token: write` required |\n| Auth mechanism | Long-lived key | Short-lived OIDC token |\n| NuGet.org setup | API key in account settings | Trusted publisher on package |\n\nThe main benefits are no secrets to rotate and scoped-down trust (only your specific workflow can publish).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8b2cca46-499a-4a84-aad3-b36030a72727","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no files in the current directory. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC) in their GitHub Actions workflow. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":676,"requestId":"E3CB:AA16B:1C963C0:20145D3:6A07BF70"},"id":"ec565826-580f-4723-8f21-2a4734655e21","timestamp":"2026-05-16T00:51:10.640Z","parentId":"66ef2d01-76ed-4b5c-b0a9-d5ddda0f1130"}
